A cozy Singapore apartment balcony at golden hour, where a young backpacker with a weathered travel rucksack sits across from an older host, both cradling steaming ceramic cups of dark coffee. In the background, a world map is pinned to the wall with small flags marking Java and Vietnam. Fresh coffee beans are scattered artfully on the wooden table between them, alongside travel guides and a worn passport. The scene is bathed in warm amber light filtering through tropical plants. Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, gentle linework, and that characteristic dreamy atmospheric quality with visible dust motes dancing in the sunlight.
